Aboitiz Power, Philex Mining: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-27T00:57:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/aboitiz-power-philex-mining-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.9 percent to
4,230.56.  Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)  : The Philippine energy company
is rated “buy” with a 12-month share price target of 34.50
pesos at CLSA Asia-Pacific Markets, which resumed coverage of
the stock. Aboitiz Power’s earnings are forecast “to accelerate
on the back of stronger demand and a recovery in generation
prices for the remainder of the year,” Raf Mercado, analyst at
CLSA, wrote in a report. The stock rose 0.4 percent to 28.10
pesos.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  : The largest Philippine metals
producer will seek approval from the Securities and Exchange
Commission and the stock exchange to listing wholly-owned Philex
Petroleum Corp., a company filing showed. The board approved to
pay as dividend one share in the petroleum unit for every eight
Philex Mining shares along with a cash dividend of 5.2 centavos
a share, the mining company said in a statement. The stock
increased 1.9 percent to 19 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
